==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[מרים|מִרְיָם]] (Miryam), from Aramaic ''[[מרים]]'' (Maryām), bitter, from a root '''מר''' (<small>MR</small>) meaning "to be bitter". (מִרְיָם, Standard Hebrew Miryam, Tiberian Hebrew Miryām) meaning either "wished for child", "bitter" or "rebellious".

===Proper noun===
'''Miriam'''

# (''Bible'') Sister of [[Moses]] and [[Aaron]], and the daughter of [[Amram]] and [[Jochebed]]. She appears first in the book of Exodus in the Hebrew Bible wherein she was born in Egypt when the Jews were kept as slaves by the Egyptians. Cf. [[myrrhe]].
# A female [[given name]]. [[Maria]] is the Greek form of this name.

